ce:section.ce:para:
The phosphorescence quantum yield (ΦΔ
                        ) was determined by monitoring singlet oxygen emission around 1275 nm in acetonitrile, following a modified McKenzie et al. protocol [88]. Mono-exponential decay was ensured by performing measurements under low-energy conditions, and kinetic data were analyzed accordingly. Using tris(bipyridine)ruthenium(II) chloride (ΦΔ
                        = 0.57 in acetonitrile) [89], as a reference, the singlet oxygen quantum yield (ΦΔ
                        ) of the synthesized perylene-functionalized acridine derivative (Per FACD) was found to be 0.22. This value aligns with previously reported ΦΔ
                         values for perylenylethynyl derivatives (0.28–0.45) [90], and falls within the broader range observed for perylene photosensitizers developed for antiviral photodynamic therapy (PDT) by Strakova et al. (0.07–0.60) [91].
